{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Planning decomposition is complete and intentionally remains open/unclaimed until implementation begins.\n\nHierarchy and order:\n\n- `2c14-fa5f-1228-4e02` — complete the generic code-review project-criterion runtime seam.\n  - `8a4b-e8b6-1bf9-48d8` — reproduce and repair the integration defect.\n- `225a-323c-a9f6-436b` — author `project.review-phase-boundaries` and its balanced eval corpus; depends on `2c14`.\n- `9447-b31c-e0b7-446d` — run the live Gerrit dogfood probe; depends on both `2c14` and `225a`.\n\nThe seam defect is verified in the current code: project routing can describe a code-review criterion, but Round-A fan-in does not dynamically execute activated project prompts; eval/CLI resolution is plan-review-biased and the code-review solver admits a closed prompt set; Pass 3 does not consistently consume one repository-effective routing view. The bug owns a generic, gate-keyed repair with no `project.review-phase-boundaries` special case.\n\nRollout remains advisory-only: `block_threshold: 0.90`, `blocking_enabled: false`. Existing `suggested_fix` support is grandfathered debt; unchanged uses are ignored and new/expanded Pass-1 remediation is a violation. A future blocking promotion requires a separate reviewed ticket backed by accumulated Gerrit evidence."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784329419948733001,"uuid":"b801db19-05c0-41f4-9714-362f7e7eb846"}